<br>
If you are a rogue... in a 6 person xp group... this proposed change really doesn't make that much difference.  However, in a raid environment where there are 6 rogues at an encounter, it makes a HUGE deal.  The -loop problem that vestas described is exactly what will happen.  Rogues will constantly be evading onto each other and changing the top 3 slots on the aggro list, until they are all dead.  <br>
<br>
I really don't see a problem with evade right now as it currently stands.  You can still fail evade.  And when you are aggro getting hit, due to lag and timing of when you hit hide, you can have it interrupted.<br>
<br>
In a fight with a level 60+ mob... when a rogue becomes top on the aggro list, you get ONE chance evade unless you use a disc.  If a mob turns on me, I know my time is over... unless I can evade or move out of range and hope that lowers me.  But remember... you can't do both at the same time (thx hide==evade).  I preempt evade every chance I can, and sometimes even that is not enough to keep me off the top of the list.<br>
<br>
Just some more things to consider for everyone who wants to someday play their rogue in a high level environment...<br>
<br>
