<br>
A little more detail on the mechanics of the current proposal:<br>
<br>
Rogue has earned 10000 hate, top of the hate list.<br>
<br>
Warrior has earned 5000 hate, 2nd on the hate list.<br>
<br>
Monk has earned 2500 hate, 3rd on the hate list.<br>
<br>
Rogue evades, moves to #2 on the hate list and his actual hate is adjusted to be between the old #2 and #3, his new hate value would be 3750.  Warrior now has more hate than the rogue by a decent margin. <br>
<br>
Now, those numbers are very arbitrary, but the formula remains the same no matter what the actual hate value was for the #1, 2 and 3 spots. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> (#2hate-#3hate)/2(+#3hate)=Rogue Evade hate.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> This formula only applies if the rogue is #1 on the hate list. <br>
<br>
There are also a couple more safeguards in place, if the #2 and #3 have the exact hate value the rogue slips in a few points lower than that value. The same applies if all three highest hate values are equal.<br>
<br>
<br>
To keep you from reaching the top of the hate list, you can pre-evade, each sucessful Evade will lower hate by 10% of your total.  <br>
<br>
To me, pre-evading will be the best method of controlling hate.  If you find yourself at the top of the hate list even with pre-evading, you may want to rethink your placement, weapons, group makeup, etc. <br>
<br>
That's part of being responsible for your damage.  If you don't manage this well, you can end up #1, which means you will get attacked.  But you still have a way to minimize the amount of time you are the target once this occurs.<br>
<br>
The worst case scenario is when there are three rogues in a fight with similar damage output, all three could rotate in and out of the top spot if they are not careful. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uminionx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MinionX</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/01 10:25:21 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Changes to what we are proposing to Evade +more.</span><hr size=1> "It won't be implemented badly, it will be tested before it goes live."<br>
